      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "When calculating the power of an experiment (power = probability of\nrejecting the null hypothesis when a specific alternative is true) the\nnon-central F statistic becomes important.  When the null hypothesis is\ntrue, the F statistic follows a central F distribution. When the null\nhypothesis is not true, then it follows a non-central F statistic."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nWeisstein, Eric W. \"Noncentral F-Distribution.\"\nFrom MathWorld--A Wolfram Web Resource.\nhttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/NoncentralF-Distribution.html",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nWikipedia, \"Noncentral F-distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noncentral_F-distribution",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "In a study, testing for a specific alternative to the null hypothesis\nrequires use of the Noncentral F distribution. We need to calculate the\narea in the tail of the distribution that exceeds the value of the F\ndistribution for the null hypothesis.  We'll plot the two probability\ndistributions for comparison."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "dfnum = 3 # between group deg of freedom"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "dfden = 20 # within groups degrees of freedom"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "nonc = 3.0"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "nc_vals = we.random.noncentral_f(dfnum, dfden, nonc, 1000000)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "NF = we.histogram(nc_vals, bins=50, density=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "c_vals = we.random.f(dfnum, dfden, 1000000)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "F = we.histogram(c_vals, bins=50, density=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(F[1][1:], F[0])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(NF[1][1:], NF[0])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
